    {
      "id": "f498712d25061ea21c9ef4a6b8238cca7db5db82",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-11-05 18:26:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nWhile it looks like the patch is good, it is clear that this functionality is not being tested anywhere.  We need to add a test that uses the \"lfsck_start -C\" option and verifies that this is actually working.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e1601f6d28ff7abcabc4a05216d08a46cd8d6207",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2014-11-05 19:51:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIn 'lctl lfsck_start' you can use the --create_mdtobj flag or the -C flag to create the lost MDT-objects. In this case, the '-C' flag works and is being tested in sanity-lfsck, but the --create_mdtobj flag does not work. In sanity-lfsck, we only test the short form of all flags. So, in sanity-lfsck, we test -C, -c, -r, etc. and not --create_mdtobj, --create_ostobj, --reset, respectively. \n\nSo, do we need to add additional tests in sanity-lfsck to test both flag types?\n\nNote: It looks like window size (-w), dryrun (-n) and error (-e) are not being tested in sanity-lfsck. Maybe this was discussed previously and there's a reason they aren't tested for.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "065c52b48a067a34189ef75ce7c3a0243792be9d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2014-11-05 20:00:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLet me amend that. I'm not sure the -C option is working, but it is being used and tested in sanity-lfsck in tests 23a, 23b, and 23c.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3fd6c1403f6b1602498abf40dc8e8380c94403c3",
